com.mmontuori.binarytree

Class Node<A,B>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mmontuori.binarytree.Node<A,B>
  • Type Parameters:
    A - is the object to be used as the node key
    B - is the actual object value to store in the binary tree

    public class Node<A,B>
extends java.lang.Object
    Node is the main container for binary search tree nodes. The class contains a key, a value, a left and a right child. Node is used by BinaryTree as the main container.
    Author:
    Michael Montuori
